cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with network measurement and topology reconstruction of the Bitcoin network, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also discusses potential vulnerabilities related to network topology, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The use of orphan transactions to reconstruct the topology could also place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper's focus on measurement and data analysis could also suggest the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the use of cryptocurrency networks could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category.
